Using LaTex packages


Introduction

LaTex offers a lot of functions by default, but sometimes you need to use packages.
To import a package in LaTeX simply add \usepackage directive on the preamble of your document


Sample
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{PACKAGENAME}
\begin{document}
% contents
\end{document}
Summary

Packages add new functions to LaTeX
All packages must be included in the preamble

Basic Document


Basic layout

Creating documents with LaTeX is simple and fun
A basic example document can be created with the following code

\documentclass{article}
\begin{document}
  Hello World!
\end{document}

Title Page
\documentclass{article}
\title{My first document}
\date{2024-11-04}
\author{John Doe}
\begin{document}
  \maketitle
  \newpage
  Hello World!
\end{document}
Summary

A document has a preamble and document part.

Sectioning Elements


Syntax
\section{} % adding a section
\subsection{} % add subsection
\subsubsection{} % add subsubsection
\paragraph{} % add paragraph
\subparagraph{} % add subparagraph
Example Code
\documentclass{article}
\title{Title of my document}
\date{2024-11-04}
\author{John Doe}
\begin{document}
    \maketitle
    \section{Section}
    Hello World!
    \subsection{Subsection}
    Structuring a document is easy!
\end{document}

